docs.lead_paragraph: RICHMOND, Ky. — President Trump on Saturday anointed Mitch McConnell, the Senate majority leader, as “the greatest leader in history,” an exchange that underscored how an often contentious dynamic has been smoothed by Republicans’ success in seating Justice Brett M. Kavanaugh and a host of other conservative judges on the nation’s courts.

headline.main: A Court Victory Heals All Wounds: Trump Calls McConnell ‘the Greatest Leader in History’
headline.print_headline: At Kentucky Rally, Signs of a Mended Rift

docs.lead_paragraph: LOUISVILLE, Ky. — Abortion rights groups, bracing for an assault on federal legal protections under a Supreme Court moved to the right by Justice Brett M. headline.main: With Kavanaugh on Court, Abortion Rights Groups Sharpen Their Focus on the States
headline.print_headline: Abortion Rights Groups: ‘Now We’re in Overdrive’

docs.abstract: Federal immigration agents apprehended about 2,900 fewer migrants at the border with Mexico in July. The drop follows a springtime spike in arrests.

docs.abstract: A Texas judge’s ruling that the Affordable Care Act is unconstitutional may not stand, but it will elevate health care as a pressing topic in a divided Washington.
docs.snippet: A Texas judge’s ruling that the Affordable Care Act is unconstitutional may not stand, but it will elevate health care as a pressing topic in a divided Washington.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The decision by a federal judge in Texas to strike down all of the Affordable Care Act has thrust the volatile debate over health care onto center stage in a newly divided capital, imperiling the insurance coverage of millions of Americans while delivering a possible policy opening to Democrats.

headline.main: Ruling Striking Down Obamacare Moves Health Debate to Center Stage
headline.print_headline: Democrats Warn  Of ‘5-Alarm Fire’  Over Health Law
